{
  "openapi": "3.0.0",
  "info": {
    "version": "5.0",
    "title": "av_microservice_finance",
    "description": "Finance m/s for processing and tracking lending of Airtime, MoMo, and Data\n<style>\n  table {\n  border: 2px solid powderblue;\n  }\n</style>  \n<h2>Release Notes</h2>\n\n<table>\n<th>Version</th><th>Detail</th>\n<tr><td>5.0.149</td><td>Logging issues fixed when logging all even though set to error.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>5.0.132</td><td>Deprecated queued advance state (statusId=6)<br><b><font color = red>DevOps, this requires renaming fn_cancel_unconfirmed_queued to fn_cancel_unconfirmed_advances in the scheduler job</td></tr>\n<tr><td>5.0.131</td><td>Introduced deactivationdate in subscriber column to track when sub was churned</font></b></td></tr>\n<tr><td>5.0.130</td><td>Reconcile endpoints are now only allowed to update advance and payment date once</td></tr>\n<tr><td>5.0.114</td><td>Optional sourceId parameter on addRepayment</br>Optional updatedExternalRef parameter on reconcileAdvance</br>reconcilePaymentConsolidated response includes previous reconciled minutely status</td></tr> \n<tr><td>5.0.108</td><td>First release</td></tr>\n</table>\n\n\n<h2>Introduction</h2>\n\nThe <b>Finance</b> micro-service exposes end points to add loans, add repayments, and a number of other features required to run and manage a lending system.\n\n\n<br>\n<font color=red><b>Notes on the SETTING table:</b></font><br>\nBelow is a list of important entries in the <b>setting</b> table\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tr><th><b>Item</b></th><th align=center><b>Example value</b></th><th><b>Description</b></th></tr>\n<tr><td>SOURCE_OF_TRUTH</td><td align=center border=1>1</td><td>If the MNO is the source of truth, we record the payment records as we receive it (1 - MNO; 2 - AV) - meaning the entire payment amount is allocated to the oldest open advance if the advanceid was not supplied. If AV is the source of truth, payments are allocated to open advances from the oldest advance first to the most recent</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td class='normal' valign='top'>REPAY_ORDER</td>\n<td class='normal' valign='top' align='center'>3,2,1</td>\n<td>The order payments are allocated per advance to the different charges. I.e. 3,2,1 means interest (3) is paid first, then service fee(2), and lastly the advance portion(1)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class='normal' valign='top'>URL_DOSENDSMS</td>\n<td class='normal' valign='top' align='center'>http://127.0.0.1:81/doSendSMS</td>\n<td>The URL for sending SMSes created in the interest notification and collection messages jobs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class='normal' valign='top'>LENDING_CEILING</td>\n<td class='normal' valign='top' align='center'>1000</td>\n<td>The total currency value of open advances that a subscriber can have at any given time</td>\n</tr>    \n</table>\n\n<font color=red><b>Notes on collection messages (bad debt/payment reminder messages):</b></font><br>\nSingle open loans:\nfn_send_collection_messages\n</br>\n\\<AMOUNT> - outstanding amount on the loan\n</br>\n\\<DUEDATE> - the date that the loan is due\n</br>\n\\<LOANAMOUNT> - total value of the loan\n</br>\n\\<DAYS> - how many days the loan is overdue\n</br></br>\nMultiple open loans:\nfn_send_collection_messages_open_to_buy</br>\n\\<AMOUNT> - the total amount of all loans that is/will be due on the given day\n</br>\n\\<DUEDATE> - date when the loans will be due on the given day\n</br>\n\\<DAYS_OVERDUE> - how many days loans are overdue\n</br>\n\\<DUE_IN_DAYS> - how many days before due date is reached\n</br>\n\\<TOTAL_AMOUNT> - the total amount of loans that is still outstanding\n</br>\n",
    "x-jentic-source-url": "https://api.swaggerhub.com/apis/airvantage-team/av_microservice_finance/5.0/swagger.json"
  },
  "paths": {
    "/addAdvance": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_addAdvance",
        "summary": "Creates and registers a subscriber advance.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "Adds a new loan/advance for a given MSISDN.</br>\nReturns an <u>advanceID</u> in the JSON response.  \n</br>\n<b>Note:</b>Subsequent calls to repay this loan (<i>/addRepayment</i>) will require this <u>advanceID</u>. If the advanceId is NOT specified, the payment will go towards paying off the oldest advance.\n</br></br>\n<b>Ignoring duplicate addAdvance requests:</b>\nA mechanism exists to ignore requests that are exactly the same and are received within a certain amount of time from each other. CACHE_LIVENESS_SECONDS can be set to specify how many seconds the same request should be ignored if it is already received previously.",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "qualifiedAmt",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Amount the person qualified to borrow",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "default": "loanAmt"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "chosenAmt",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Amount person chose to borrow",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "default": "loanAmt"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "channelId",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "1- UNKNOWN<br>\n2 - USSD</br>\n3 - SMS<br>\n4 - ZERO BALANCE",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "default": 1
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "serviceId",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "An optional id to identify the service that this advance is for e.g. autotopup advance",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "default": 1
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "serviceAmt",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "An optional amount that will be added as the service fee portion",
            "schema": {
              "type": "number",
              "default": 0
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "externalref",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "An optional external reference to link the advance to a third party's system",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "default": ""
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "term",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The number of terms in which this advance will be repaid. ",
            "schema": {
              "type": "number",
              "default": 1
            }
          },
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/trait_queryParamEntitytype_entityType"
          },
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/trait_queryParamLoanamount_loanAmt"
          },
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/trait_queryParamLoandate_loanDate"
          },
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/trait_queryParamMsisdn_msisdn"
          },
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/trait_queryParamProfiletierid_profileTierId"
          },
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/trait_queryParamRepaydate_repayDate"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "success": {
                      "type": "boolean"
                    },
                    "detail": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "responseCode": {
                          "type": "string"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "Success": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": true,
                      "detail": {
                        "advanceId": 4,
                        "comment": "Success"
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  "Validation error": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": false,
                      "detail": {
                        "message": "Missing parameter for msisdn",
                        "responseCode": "03"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/addRepayment": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_addRepayment",
        "summary": "Adds an advance repayment.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "Adds a repayment (full/partial) towards a loan/advance.</br> </br> There are <b>3 payment allocation strategies</b>:</br> 1. Advanceid was supplied in the request</b> - The payment will only be allocated to this one advance.</br> 2. Advanceid was not supplied and AV is source of truth (see setting table) - The payment will be allocated to multiple advances, from oldest to most recent.</br> 3. Advanceid was not supplied and MNO is source of truth (see setting table) - The payment will be allocated to the oldest open advance only.</br>\n\n<b><font color=red>Note:</font></b> \n</br>If an advance id was supplied, then if that advance is in status <b>1</b> (unconfirmed) or status <b>3</b> (cancelled) that receives a payment, it will be updated to status <b>2</b> (confirmed) </br></br>",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "amount",
            "description": "Amount to allocate to the msisdn / advance id - Takes precedence over the loanAmt and serviceAmt. So if this parameter is supplied, its value will be used instead of the values of loanAmt and serviceAmt\n",
            "required": false,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "rechargeDate",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "TimeStamp on the IN",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "date",
              "pattern": "yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm:ss"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "paymentTransactionId",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Internal payment identifier.",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "loanAmt",
            "deprecated": true,
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Amount being allocated to repaying the Loan portion. This will be deprecated and replaced by the amount parameter.\n",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "number"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "advanceId",
            "description": "If supplied, the amount will be allocated to the advance with this advance id\n",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "msisdn",
            "description": "If the advanceId is omitted, then the amount will be applied to the open advances associated with this msisdn\n",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "serviceAmt",
            "deprecated": true,
            "description": "Amount being allocated to repaying the service fee portion. This will be deprecated and replaced by the amount parameter.\n",
            "required": false,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "statusId",
            "description": "The statusId that the payment must be inserted with.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "sourceId",
            "description": "The sourceId indicates the originator of the payment. Meaning of values:\n 0 - undefined; \n 1 - ussd initiated; \n 2 - online (deposit notification) (deposit initiated);\n 3 - reconcile process (minute cdr);\n 4 - reconcile process (daily cdr);\n 5 - payment checker;\n 6 - manual process;\n 7 - sweep initiated\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "default": 0
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "result": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "status": {
                          "type": "boolean"
                        },
                        "msisdn": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "comment": {
                          "type": "string"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "Success": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": true,
                      "detail": {
                        "paymentId": "17",
                        "comment": "Success"
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  "Validation error": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": false,
                      "detail": {
                        "message": "service fee repay amount and loan fee repayment cannot both be zero ",
                        "responseCode": "03"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/addCharge": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_addCharge",
        "summary": "Adds a charge against the specified advance.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "Adds a charge towards an advance.</br>",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "amount",
            "description": "Amount to allocate to the msisdn / advance id\n",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "advanceId",
            "description": "The amount will be allocated to the advance with this advance id\n",
            "in": "query",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "transactionType",
            "description": "The type of charge i.e 1 = advance, 2 = service fee, 3 = interest\n",
            "in": "query",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "chargeDate",
            "description": "The date of the charge. If omitted, the current time will be used.\n",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "result": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "status": {
                          "type": "boolean"
                        },
                        "msisdn": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "comment": {
                          "type": "string"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "Success": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": true,
                      "detail": {
                        "message": "Success",
                        "responseCode": "01"
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  "Validation error": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": false,
                      "detail": {
                        "message": "Missing amount",
                        "responseCode": "03"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/addSubscriber": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_addSubscriber",
        "summary": "Adds a subscriber to the Lending schema.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "Creates a new subscriber record for a given MSISDN.</br>\nIf the MSISDN already existed, it won't be added again",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "actionDate",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Activation Date </br>yyyy/mm/dd",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/trait_queryParamMsisdn_msisdn"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "201": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "success": {
                      "type": "boolean"
                    },
                    "detail": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "responseCode": {
                          "type": "string"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "Success": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": true,
                      "detail": {
                        "advanceId": 4,
                        "comment": "Success"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/getMsisdnList": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_getMsisdnList",
        "summary": "Returns a list of msisdns based on advance details.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "Returns a list of msisdn matching the specified advance criteria - WORK IN PROGRESS",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "advanceAgeDays",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Return msisdns with advances open for this many days AND older",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "statusId",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Return msisdns with advances in this status",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "limit",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Limit the returned list to this many msisdns",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "offset",
            "required": false,
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The starting point of the list",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "201": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "success": {
                      "type": "boolean"
                    },
                    "detail": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "responseCode": {
                          "type": "string"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "Success": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": true,
                      "detail": {
                        "msisdnList": [
                          {
                            "msisdn": "12345644444"
                          },
                          {
                            "msisdn": "22225554488"
                          },
                          {
                            "msisdn": "22225554488"
                          }
                        ],
                        "responseCode": "01"
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  "Empty list": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": true,
                      "detail": {
                        "msisdnList": [],
                        "responseCode": "01"
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  "Failure": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": false,
                      "detail": {
                        "message": "Missing parameter for statusId",
                        "responseCode": "03"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/getBalanceEntity": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_getBalanceEntity",
        "summary": "Get entity type balance for a subscriber.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "Returns the total balance for a particular msisdn and entitytype",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "msisdn",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "entityType",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "referenceDate",
            "required": true,
            "description": "Only advances before this date will be considered",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "201": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "success": {
                      "type": "boolean"
                    },
                    "detail": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "responseCode": {
                          "type": "string"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "Success": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": true,
                      "detail": {
                        "totalBalance": "20.00"
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  "Failure": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": false,
                      "detail": {
                        "responseCode": "00",
                        "message": "Failure to retrieve balance"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/churnSubscriber": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_churnSubscriber",
        "summary": "Deactivates this subscsriber.  Future references to this MSISDN will create a new subscriber.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "Marks the current subscriber associated with this MSISDN as inactive <strike>and creates a new subscriber</strike>.  All subsequent transactions against the MSISDN will be linked to a newly created subscriber.\n\n<b>Note:</b></br>\nFor the sake of optimal performance, this end-point does not bother checking for the existence of an MSISDN before trying to <i>churn</i> it.  It simply updates the <i>subscriber</i>, setting the status to INACTIVE for the given MSISDN (if it exists).",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/trait_queryParamMsisdn_msisdn"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "result": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "status": {
                          "type": "boolean"
                        },
                        "msisdn": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "comment": {
                          "type": "string"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "response": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": true,
                      "detail": {
                        "message": "Active sub doesn't exist. Nothing churned",
                        "responseCode": "01"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/doMSISDNSwap": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_doMSISDNSwap",
        "summary": "Changes MSISDN whilst retaining subscriber history.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "This endpoint is used to update the suscriber table in the lending microservice, whenever there is a change in the subscriber's msisdn",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "msisdn",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "newMsisdn",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "success": {
                      "type": "boolean"
                    },
                    "detail": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "responseCode": {
                          "type": "string"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "response": {
                    "value": {
                      "success": false,
                      "detail": {
                        "message": "Could not swap msisdn",
                        "responseCode": "00"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/getAdvanceHistory": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GET_getAdvanceHistory",
        "summary": "Returns advance history.",
        "tags": [
          "Public"
        ],
        "description": "This endpoint returns all the advances associated with the provided msisdn. Advances can be filtered by entityType, status and age by supplying the parameters below. </br> Note: The endpoint was originally used by the profiler gui to get a subscriber's lending history ( advance history).",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "msisdn",
            "description": "The subscriber's msisdn",
            "in": "query",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "entityType",
            "description": "Return only advances that have this entityType",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "advanceAgeDays",
            "description": "Return only advances that are this many days old and older",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "status",
            "description": "Return only advances that have this status id",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
